The paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a non-convex optimization framework for sparse representation, which involves signal processing and optimization techniques, and can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of patch-based methods, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
